article.headline: Niagara 86, Marist 67
article.story: LEWISTON, N.Y. -- In a Jan. 15 story on the Marist-Niagara game, The Associated Press erroneously reported that Devin Price, Adam Kemp and Chavaughan Lewis were the leading scorers for Niagara and that Antoine Mason was the leading scorer for Marist. The story should have said that Price, Kemp and Lewis were the leading scorers for Marist and that Mason was the leading scorer for Niagara.
